{
  "text": "A similar reaction can be carried out in CdS system with elemental S as the sulfur source [CITATION_1] . Myristic acid (MA) is used as a capping ligand, and 2,2\u2032-dithiobisbenzothiazole (MBTS) is added to promote sulfur reactivity. A series of experiment conditions are also investigated to find out the optimized synthesis condition. With the acid-to-Cd ratio fixed (2:1), a ratio of (1-2)Cd/1S and (8-32)S/1MBTS, a growth temperature of 220-350\u00b0C is determined to be ideal for QD growth. The obtained CdS QD has a FWHM of 17-22 nm and a quantum yield up to 30 %.",
